SIMPLE: grandeur
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Grandeur
<hw>Gran"deur</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr.
<ets>grand</ets>. See <er>Grand</er>.]</ety> <def>The state or quality
of being grand; vastness; greatness; splendor; magnificence;
stateliness; sublimity; dignity; elevation of thought or expression;
nobility of action.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Nor doth this <qex>grandeur</qex> and majestic show⟦br⟧
Of luxury . . . allure mine eye.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Sublimity; majesty; stateliness; augustness;
loftiness. See <er>Sublimity</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Grandevity</ent>⟦br⟧
